        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Your father was the Great Captain of the Spanish Reconquista and in his retirement you poured over his books and listened to his war stories with awe and wonder.  When he died you inheirited his many titles, but as a young girl of 16 you gained none of his power.  You even had to marry a cousin to retain his name and holdings.  Your life may have ended as a footnote, a child bride dead after child birth, but your Sire came to you as a shadow and and brought you into his world instead.  The Sabbat was struggling to survive and he needed your father's secrets and the loyalty of his mortal captains. You were the key to both and with your sire you sailed to Mexico, then goverened by the mortal Cortez. In the Sabbat's early days you discovered Lilith and the truth of your divine gift, your Sire encouraged such exploration in his pack and it was only after the sect was wracked with civil war that the Church of Caine the Father became absolute.  Your sire is gone now, destroyed 2 decades ago during Temoch's Reformation of the Black Hand.  Now you lead the Cardine Scorso and intend to claim the Archdioceses of San Diego for yourself, despite what everyone else may think."
        ],
